  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbd\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dda \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca 1000\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "1000 liters of oil at the Puttalam black market",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that two specialists of the Puttalam Base Hospital have bought a liter of petrol for their cars on two occasions at a price of Rs. 1,000.",
        "It is said that he had to go home suddenly and had to buy a liter of petrol for Rs. 1000 on his own.",
        "It is said that the petrol was delivered from a place near the city of Puttalam.",
        "It is learned that both the specialists had tried their best to get petrol from petrol stations but had not been able to do so and had to buy petrol from those who sell it at such a high price.",
        "He says that he has informed some of his friends about this due to the need to go home soon.",
        "He says that due to his need, one specialist doctor later bought 30 liters of fuel for Rs. 30,000."
      ],
